com.alexgilleran.icesoap.parser.impl

Class XPathPullParserImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.alexgilleran.icesoap.parser.impl.XPathPullParserImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    XPathPullParser

    public class XPathPullParserImpl
extends Object
implements XPathPullParser
    Wrapper for XmlPullParser for XPath operations. Basically this acts in much the same manner as an XmlPullParser, but keeps track of the current position in the document as an XPathElement, which can be retrieved at any time. It also changes the parser so that attributes are an event.
    Author:
    Alex Gilleran

      • getCurrentValue

        public String getCurrentValue()
        Get the String value of the current node, whether attribute or text. For a text node, this will move to the end of the text node after getting the value. Note that if the event is XPathPullParser.ATTRIBUTE, this will only ever return the value of the attribute - get the name with XPathPullParser.getCurrentElement().
        Specified by:
        getCurrentValue in interface XPathPullParser
        Returns:
        The string value of the current node.

      • next

        public int next()
         throws XMLParsingException
        Delegates to XmlPullParser.next() - gets the next event from the pull parser. Note that although this is much the same as XmlPullParser.next(), this treats attribute values as events in their own right, rather than just tags. Attribute events will return the value XPathPullParser.ATTRIBUTE.
        Specified by:
        next in interface XPathPullParser
        Returns:
        The type of the next event, as an int.
        Throws:
        XMLParsingException - If an error is encountered in the XML.
        See Also:
        XmlPullParser.next()
